OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FClass sizes grow to keep up
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwith GCSE resits           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Colleges in England say they are having
OL,6, to expand class sizes and hire exam    
OL,7, halls to cope with a rising number of  
OL,8, pupils taking compulsory GCSE resits.  
OL,10,FSome are rehiring former teachers,     
OL,11,Faccording to the Association of        
OL,12,FColleges (AoC), as an extra 60,000     
OL,13,Fstudents prepare to resit English and  
OL,14,Fmaths, many of them in two weeks' time.
OL,16,FChanges to grading this year meant a   
OL,17,Fhigher proportion of students failed.  
OL,19,FThe government says it is investing    
OL,20,Fmore money in colleges.                
